 :tx/rationale "Create task: SOUND-NAN: NaN propagation guards in graph.rs and bilateral.rs. CONTEXT: Hand-written eigensolver (Jacobi rotation) in query/graph.rs has hardcoded iteration limit with no convergence flag. Downstream computations — Fiedler value, Cheeger constant, spectral gap, Renyi entropy, Ricci curvature, PageRank — can propagate NaN from division by zero (e.g., PageRank on graph with zero outgoing edges, spectral_gap = lambda_2/lambda_max where lambda_max=0, Phi normalization where entity_count=0). In Rust, NaN comparisons are always false (NaN > x = false, NaN < x = false), causing silent logic errors in routing score ranking, boundary threshold checks, task priority ordering. 40 unwrap() calls in graph.rs amplify risk. RATIONALE: NaN is the only value in Rust that violates trichotomy. Any comparison-based logic that encounters NaN produces wrong results silently. A single NaN in the eigensolver output corrupts every downstream metric. APPROACH: (1) Add is_finite() guards on eigensolver output in spectral_decomposition_adaptive(). Return eigenvalues as Vec<f64> with a convergence bool. If !converged, log warning and return fallback (identity spectrum). (2) Add is_finite() check at every division site in: spectral_gap computation, cheeger(), ricci_curvature_adaptive(), ricci_summary(), von_neumann_entropy(). Replace NaN with 0.0 or None as appropriate. (3) Add convergence flag to EigenDecomposition return type. (4) In bilateral.rs fitness computation, guard all division by max(denominator, 1) or equivalent. (5) Add proptest: for any valid adjacency matrix (non-negative, finite entries), all spectral metrics are finite. ACCEPTANCE: (A) proptest passes — no NaN in output for any finite input. (B) Degenerate cases tested: empty graph (0 nodes), single node, fully disconnected, fully connected, zero-weight edges. (C) Each guard has a unit test for the specific NaN-producing input. (D) No behavior change for well-formed inputs. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/query/graph.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/bilateral.rs. TRACES-TO: INV-BILATERAL-001 (F(S) convergence), INV-QUERY-002 (query determinism)."
